    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Feature request: it would be nice to avoid needing to maintain a separate pxd file.  Something like either a `@cython.export` decorator or a top-of-module `# cython: just_export_everything=True` declaration.  Would this be feasible and/or accepted if a PR were forthcoming?",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "OWNER",
            "body": "There is https://github.com/cython/cython/blob/master/Cython/Compiler/Options.py#L112 , but that applies globally and must be set on the cimporting (rather than cimported) module's compilation so isn't widely advertised. In addition, sometimes it's desirable to export just a subset, and can save on compilation time as well. \r\n\r\nA pragma at the top of a pyx file is an interesting proposal however. ",
